        <div class="print-information print-qrcode-container">
            <p class="print-qrcode-label">QR Code Link to This Post</p>
            <div class="print-qrcode" data-location="https://providence.craigslist.org/apa/d/cranston-beautiful-bedroom-home-rare/7514484543.html"></div>
        </div>
Why rent an apartment complex or mill houseing when you can have this 1 bedroom home with full bath-kitchen living and dining area.<br>
Partial finished lower level<br>
Fenced in back yard<br>
Off street parking<br>
Super energy efficient boiler system with hot water on demand<br>
Plenty of natural daylight<br>
Located on very quiet street<br>
minitutes from the johnston Line<br>
Hardwood floors throughout<br>
Fridge Stove Dishwasher Over the stove Microwave.<br>
Good size living area. basement with rear access bulkhead.<br>
Quiet street- Close to Major highways, 15 mins from Providence Capital city<br>
Washer Dryer hook ups- May consider supplying washer and dryer.<br>
Lawncare provided by owner<br>
<br>
<br>
Must be able to produce good letter of recomendation from previous landlord if you are considered ?<br>
We are looking for REAL honest tenants that just want their private space and enjoy their Living. Tired of the scammers and time wasters.<br>
If you are to be considered please be prepared to provide the following after or prior to the showing of the unit<br>
-Provide documentation that you are not or have not been evicted in the last 4 yrs<br>
-Provide proof of current steady employment with income to support rent<br>
-be able to pass a soft background check<br>
-be able to provide security(1525.00) and 1st months rent upon lease signing  <br>
-If you are currently applying for rent relief from the state then that is OK However, Rent Relief approval can not be contigent on signing lease and money for security and 1st month. We will gladly apply state rental relief checks to forarding months approved by rent relief.<br>
<br>
This is a GREAT single family 1 bedroom home in a quiet area.<br>
Cranston Johnston Line<br>
Minutes from ALL major highways<br>
American Disabilities Act Pets with Correct Certified Papers are always welcome. Other pets may be considered<br>
This Home s available by August 1st<br>
heat and electric not included<br>
<br>
In regards to Housing Vouchers/Section 8.  To my knowledge Cranston Housing authority will not approve this home because the rent amount is higher than the payment standard allowed. Please feel free to inquire with Housing authority before responding. We do have other properties that do qulify for the Housing Assistance but unfortunately are not available at this time.  Also upon your inquiry with the Housing Authority if you are told the total allowable amount is less than 1525.00 per month, PLEASE DO NOT ask if you can pay us the difference . That is against the law and we wil not due that. I believe that currently Cranston Allowance on a 1 bed is around 1120 with utilities and 1000.00 without utilities. Please feel free to call them and confirm.<br>
<br>
Security deposit required 1525.00<br>
<br>
Please NO CALLS from rental agencies looking to list my house<br>
<br>
I understand there are limited homes avail for rent and expect alot of resposes. I will do my best to get back to your request asap<br>
<br>
If the post is active then the home is available<br>
<br>
I do not have any interior pictures curently available<br>
<br>
We have several properties that we own and manage (no other units avail at this time) We are Great Landlords and take very good care of the property. We believe in letting the tenants enjoy their privacy and we take care of the property.<br>
<br>
Looking for Long term tenants. If you sold or are selling your home and need temp housing we are not considering that <br>
<br>
Please inquire with responses to below questions<br>
Why are you moving ?<br>
Approx Length of residency you are looking for ?<br>
When are you looking to move in ?<br>
<br>
Thank You<br>
<br>
<br>
